    • Method Detail

      • compare

        public int compare(T a,
          T b)
        Compare two list items for purposes of searching. This determines the desired ordering criterion.

        The default implementation of this method casts each item to type Comparable<T>; calls the compareTo() method on item a, passing item b as the argument; and returns what the compareTo() method returns. If this is not the desired behavior, or if the list items cannot be cast to type Comparable<T>, then override this method in a subclass.

        Parameters:
        a - First list item being compared.
        b - Second list item being compared.
        Returns:
        A number less than, equal to, or greater than 0 if item a comes before, is the same as, or comes after item b in the desired ordering, false otherwise.
